---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure — Quvii"
  description="How Quvii uses Amazon Associates affiliate links + AdSense advertising. Editorial independence policy and how to identify an affiliate link."
>
  <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-ink">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-body-faint">Last updated: 2026-05-27</p>

  <div class="prose-pm max-w-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Some links on Quvii earn us a commission when you click through and
      buy. This page tells you which programs we participate in, how to
      identify an affiliate link, and how we keep recommendations honest.
    </p>

    <h2>What we participate in</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Amazon Associates</strong> (Associate ID <code>jeffzen911-20</code>).
        When we recommend a security camera in a review or buying guide, we
        link to it on Amazon. If you buy through that link, Amazon pays
        Quvii a small percentage. The price you pay is the same as if you'd
        gone to Amazon directly.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google AdSense</strong> (Publisher ID <code>pub-5523706123080113</code>).
        We run a small number of display ads on content pages. Ad placement
        is automated by Google; we never sell direct ad inventory to
        manufacturers covered on this site, which would create an obvious
        conflict.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do not currently participate in any other affiliate program. If
      that changes, this page is updated and the change is logged in the
      "Last updated" date at the top.
    </p>

    <h2>How to spot an affiliate link</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        The link tag carries <code>rel="sponsored noopener nofollow"</code>
        — the FTC + Google standard for paid placements at the HTML level.
      </li>
      <li>
        The destination URL contains our Amazon Associate ID
        (<code>tag=jeffzen911-20</code>). Hover over any "Check on Amazon"
        button and look at your browser's status bar before clicking.
      </li>
      <li>
        Articles with affiliate links display a yellow "Affiliate disclosure"
        banner at the top of the page (this same text, summarized).
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
    <p>
      Our Amazon commission rate (typically 2–4% of purchase price) is the
      same percentage across compared products within a category. That
      means we earn the same whether we put Product A or Product B at #1.
      The ranking is editorial, not financial.
    </p>
    <p>What we won't do, regardless of commission rate:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Recommend a product we wouldn't install in our own home.</li>
      <li>Hide cons. Every recommended product gets specific weaknesses called out.</li>
      <li>Re-order rankings in exchange for a higher commission tier.</li>
      <li>Publish a manufacturer's press release as if it were a review.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What if I don't want to use an affiliate link?</h2>
    <p>
      Totally fine. Go to amazon.com directly and search for the product
      name. The price is identical, you skip the cookie, and Quvii doesn't
      earn anything from your purchase. We'd still rather you came through
      us — the writing has to earn its keep — but we won't penalize you for
      opting out.
    </p>

    <h2>AdSense + ads.txt</h2>
    <p>
      Our <code>ads.txt</code> file at <a href="/ads.txt"><code>/ads.txt</code></a>
      lists every ad network we authorize to sell our display inventory.
      This is the IAB standard for preventing ad fraud — manufacturers
      can't impersonate us to push ad placement that benefits them. If you
      ever see an ad on Quvii from a network NOT listed in our ads.txt,
      let us know.
    </p>

    <h2>FTC required statement</h2>
    <p>
      <em>"As an Amazon Associate, Quvii earns from qualifying purchases."</em>
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Broken affiliate link, advertising complaint, or partnership
      inquiry: <strong>hello@quvii.com</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
